In this section, an experimental investigation of key parts of the presented design is presented. This covers the tasks of sound source localization, sound recognition and speech to text. While the sound source localization process has been developed by the authors, and the two other tasks are performed by existing work, all the tasks have been tested in situations similar to the context of usage with hearing impaired persons. 
